another problem arises when a document is made available on a user"s machine and that user is offline, in which case the document is no longer accessible.
the user may be required to search for a particular document, which some search tools such as google desktop may be a solution for local documents but will not find a document on another user"s machine.
there may even be multiple different documents in the process of being edited.
this can easily cause incorrect version to be sent or conflicts created between multiple users trying to make amendments to a document.
in some cases these documents are shared between authors, via email, to be edited.
this access may be needed for editing or simply viewing a document.
many organizations are required to author documents for various purposes, and such documents may need to be accessible by all member of the organization.
